frameDefinitions: The Means action by which a deprofiled agent (the Protagonist) has attempted to achieve a Goal, is finished and the actual outcome of the Means action has been resolved, so that it either specifically matches the Protagonist's intent (e.g. success) or does not match it (e.g. failure).

An Agent is involved in an activity whose degree of success is dependent on a parameter of the action matching a particular set of values of a continuous variable or variables (e.g. quantity, location, time).
In this frame, which is a  part of the Trial sequence, a Judge gives a Finding with respect to the Charges against the Defendant in a particular Case.
An Agent cuts a Item into Pieces using an Instrument (which may or may not be expressed).
A Dodger acts to avoid an oncoming moving Bad_entity.
An Agent succeeds or fails to interact perceptually or physically with the Target or Target_location.
frameExamples: The Longview Rangefinder is <t>accurate</t> to within one foot per hundred yards .
He was <t>convicted</t> of fraud by Judge Judy.
At the ceremony, the CEO <t>cut</t> the red ribbon hanging across the main entrance into a glorious confetti.
Mo <t>dodged</t>  the flower pot that Larry threw in disgust.
At first he shot very <t>wide</t> of his target .
listRoleDefinitions: The action that the agent undertakes to achieve the <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the agent attempts to achieve by performing the <fen>Means</fen> action.
An entity directed by the agent as part of the <fen>Means</fen> action in order to accomplish the <fen>Goal</fen>.
A participant function of an <fen>Instrument</fen> or <fen>Means</fen> in a particular event or in events of a particular kind.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt succeeds or fails
The place where <fen>Means</fen> action succeeds or fails.
The individual who tries to interact with the <fen>Target</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Means</fen> by which the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to hit a <fen>Target_value</fen>.
How closely the expected or actual location that the <fen>Instrument</fen> interacts with corresponds to the <fen>Target_value</fen>.
The object manipulated by the <fen>Agent</fen> in order to interact with the <fen>Target</fen>.
Expected or actual deviation from the <fen>Target_value</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when something hits or misses.
The place where the <fen>Agent</fen> manages or fails to interact with the <fen>Target</fen>.
The <fen>Judge</fen> (which may be the jury, judge, magistrate or court) decides on the <fen>Finding</fen>.
This role identifies the outcome of the <fen>Judge</fen>'s deliberation or consideration. Many LUs in this frame incorporate this FE.
The person who stands accused of a crime and is subject to the verdict.
This role refers to the <fen>Charges</fen> with respect to which the verdict is being given.
The <fen>Case</fen> on which the verdict is being given.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person cutting the <fen>Item</fen> into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The item which is being cut into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The <fen>Pieces</fen> are the parts of the original <fen>Item</fen> which are the result of the slicing.
When the slicing occurs.
Where the slicing takes place.
The <fen>Dodger</fen> acts to avoid an oncoming <fen>Bad_entity</fen>.
The <fen>Bad_entity</fen> is  the oncoming entity to avoid.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which the dodging occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the dodging occurs.
The individual who tries to interact with the <fen>Target</fen>.
The object manipulated by the <fen>Agent</fen> in order to interact with the <fen>Target</fen>.
The location that the <fen>Agent</fen> is attempting to access using the <fen>Instrument</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when something hits or misses.
The place where the <fen>Agent</fen> manages or fails to interact with the <fen>Target</fen>.
